<p>This is the theme for the <a href="/ad-astra-per-aspera-hub">Ad Astra Per Aspera</a> canon!</p>
<p>To use it, put the following syntax at the very top of your article.</p>
<div style="clear:both; height: 0px; font-size: 1px"></div>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;theme:ad-astra]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>There are six quoteblock colors: black (default), blue, pink, gold, purple and gray. Use them with the following code:</p>
<div class="blue">
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;blue&quot;]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div class="pink">
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;pink&quot;]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div class="gold">
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;gold&quot;]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div class="purp">
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;purp&quot;]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div class="gray">
<blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;gray&quot;]]</span></p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<p>If using the <tt><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;blockquote&quot;]]</span></tt> feature of Sigma-9, you can change the color of the blockquote by adding the color as a class after blockquote (i.e. <tt><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[div&#32;class=&quot;blockquote&#32;blue&quot;]]</span></tt>).</p>
<p>You can define <span class="h-span">highlighted (colored and bold) text</span> with <tt><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[span&#32;class=&quot;h-span&quot;]]</span></tt>. It is suggested that you use this for <span class="h-span">Item #:</span>, <span class="h-span">Object Class:</span>, <span class="h-span">Description</span>, etc.</p>
